##Eight new CPV vaccines have been evaluated in China, and the preclinical study is expected to be completed in April

On March 17,2020, the joint prevention and Control Mechanism of the State Council held a press conference to introduce the latest development of drug, vaccine and test reagent research and development. Wang Junzhi, an academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, said that the development of a new coronavirus vaccine in China is progressing smoothly in the five major technical directions. Most of the research and development teams were able to complete pre clinical studies and start clinical trials in April.

Successful vaccine development is the key to a fundamental victory in the face of major infectious diseases. Wang Junzhi said that thousands of scientists in related fields throughout the country are doing their utmost, focusing on the five technical directions of inactivated vaccine, recombinant subunit vaccine of genetic engineering, Adenovirus Vector Vaccine, attenuated influenza vector vaccine and nucleic acid vaccine, eight advantageous teams were selected and nine tasks were determined.

Wang said that so far, the five main technical directions of vaccines have made good progress in general, the first nine identified tasks have completed pre-clinical studies (that is, studies on the efficacy and safety of animals) , most of the work.

"units that have made relatively rapid progress in research and development have submitted application materials for clinical trials to the State Food and Drug Administration, and have already started work on the demonstration of clinical trial plans and recruitment of volunteers, " Wang said, after the approval of the State Food and Drug Administration in accordance with the relevant laws and regulations, clinical trials can begin. The development of the new coronavirus vaccine in China is currently in the international advanced ranks on the whole and will not be slower than that of foreign countries.

Lei Chaozi, director of the Department of Science and Technology of the Ministry of Education, said at the press conference that the Ministry of Education has mobilized scientific research teams from Xiamen University, Sichuan University, Tsinghua University, Peking University, Fudan University and other universities with research advantages since the Spring Festival, focus from the nucleic acid vaccine and other three technical routes to advance in parallel, with scientific research institutes and related enterprises to accelerate the development of new pneumonia vaccine.

Among them to nucleic acid vaccine, Lei chaozi expresses, this is the new technology of Vaccine Research and development that the whole world is in active exploration, at present the whole world does not have person to use vaccine to go on the market. Chinese universities will use the technology and scientific achievements accumulated in previous Middle East Respiratory Syndrome studies to speed up the development of nucleic acid vaccines, which will prove to be safe and effective as soon as possible.

How to ensure the safety of the vaccine is also one of the focuses of the outside world. Hatakawa, a researcher at the Institute of Laboratory Animals of the Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences, said China's vaccine development has fully considered safety and efficacy, and has been carried out in strict accordance with national laws, regulations and procedures, at present, 8 kinds of vaccines have been evaluated in Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences, and some of them have been evaluated.

Wang Junzhi said that at home and abroad for vaccine market application with strict laws and regulations and technical standards. In order to enter clinical trial, the research of pharmacy, efficacy and safety must be completed.

In Pharmaceutical Research, the main task is to establish stable production process and quality control standards to ensure the preparation of qualified vaccine samples. For Efficacy Studies, the use of animal models of infection, such as the monkey and mouse models of new coronavirus infection, to evaluate the vaccine's immunogenicity and protection after samples of the vaccine have been obtained, this result can be used to calculate the dose and procedure of Clinical Study.

In addition, vaccine development will require safety evaluation, with at least single-dose (acute) toxicity and repeated-dose (long-term toxicity) evaluations for Emerging Infectious Diseases. "In general, the first step is to produce a qualified vaccine sample, and only after it has been proved safe and effective in animal studies can it be entered into clinical trials, " Wang said.

Wang Junzhi stressed that at present, Chinese scientists in the field of vaccines are going all out in accordance with relevant regulations and technical requirements. On the one hand, they are going all out, and on the other hand, they insist on following scientific rules, and on the premise of ensuring the safety and effectiveness of vaccines, he said, to speed up the vaccine research application, "we are constantly hearing good news from them, which will provide a solid support for the global final victory over the epidemic. "

Regarding the research progress of drugs for the treatment of NCP, Zhang Xianmin, director of the Biological Center of the Ministry of Science and Technology, said at the press conference that in order to block the transformation of NCP from light and ordinary type to heavy type, the focus of the scientific and technological research group is to promote the clinical application of chloroquine phosphate, Favipiravir and traditional Chinese medicine.

Among them, Ravel has completed clinical studies and has shown good efficacy, "In view of the good safety, efficacy, drug access, after scientific research and organization experts fully demonstrated, has been formally recommended to the medical treatment group, it is recommended to be included in the diagnosis and treatment plan. "

Ravel is an RNA polymerase (RDRP) inhibitor and is a broad-spectrum anti-influenza drug. In March 2014, the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare approved fampicin tablets for use in the treatment of new and recurrent influenza. Zhang Xianmin said that in terms of safety, there has been no obvious adverse reaction since the listing of fabiraway. No significant adverse reaction was found in the clinical study of the treatment of NCP.
